                            <comment id="386480" author="JIRAUSER18707" created="Wed, 20 Sep 2023 00:50:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the info about IML. I will search extensively to see whether there are good ones for us.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ticket can be closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="386476" author="pjones" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2023 23:36:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jane&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No, IML only works up to 2.12.x - there is not a version of it that support 2.15.x. As scanning the agendas of past Lustre conferences will tell you, there are a variety of monitoring options used in the community. I cannot really recommend one over another, I think that it is a question of you just finding one that is a good match for your requirements&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
